00:38:44.770 --> 00:38:45.610
And I'm going to get back in.

00:38:45.610 --> 00:38:46.620
LUVVIE AJAYI: I'm gonna get back
in, but give me five minutes.

00:38:46.620 --> 00:38:47.630
ROLAND MARTIN: [INAUDIBLE]

00:38:47.630 --> 00:38:48.330
LUVVIE AJAYI: Your turn.

00:38:48.330 --> 00:38:49.680
ROLAND MARTIN: But I want
to go to Vint, though,

00:38:49.680 --> 00:38:51.950
because I want to do this
intersectionality piece,

00:38:51.950 --> 00:38:53.960
because it's
interesting when you

00:38:53.960 --> 00:38:57.230
talk about this intersection
of different issues.

00:38:57.230 --> 00:39:00.530
I think about-- and again,
I brought the 14th Amendment

00:39:00.530 --> 00:39:03.334
again, equal protection clause.

00:39:03.334 --> 00:39:05.750
The Supreme Court, when they
decided same sex marriage was

00:39:05.750 --> 00:39:10.820
based upon that, what was
interesting is BYP100 had done

00:39:10.820 --> 00:39:15.340
a shout out where
they said, look, OK,

00:39:15.340 --> 00:39:16.870
y'all get same sex marriage.

00:39:16.870 --> 00:39:18.830
That ain't what we
concerned about.

00:39:18.830 --> 00:39:21.050
And it was interesting
because I had

00:39:21.050 --> 00:39:23.220
black gay folks who
were saying, that

00:39:23.220 --> 00:39:25.100
ain't number one on our list.

00:39:25.100 --> 00:39:27.850
And I've had to deal with
African-Americans, same

00:39:27.850 --> 00:39:31.550
you're talking Jose
Antonio Vargas, Asians,

00:39:31.550 --> 00:39:35.330
Latinos, who are gay, who are in
this movement saying, hold it.

00:39:35.330 --> 00:39:39.720
How we all gay, but then we're
still fighting marginalization

00:39:39.720 --> 00:39:42.770
in the LGBT movement-- in
the equality movement that

00:39:42.770 --> 00:39:45.200
practices inequality?

00:39:45.200 --> 00:39:47.546
So as we begin to
move forward, I

00:39:47.546 --> 00:39:49.670
think we're going to see
even more of those battles

00:39:49.670 --> 00:39:51.044
where all of a
sudden it's not as

00:39:51.044 --> 00:39:56.620
clear as black,
Asian, Latino, women.

00:39:56.620 --> 00:39:58.910
Now it's going to
be things crossing.

00:39:58.910 --> 00:40:03.500
VINT CERF: Look, there are
dozens, if not more, categories

00:40:03.500 --> 00:40:05.315
in which everyone fits.

00:40:05.315 --> 00:40:09.350
And a lot of those categories
will put you into minority.

00:40:09.350 --> 00:40:12.050
And so it seems to
me absolutely clear

00:40:12.050 --> 00:40:14.810
that everything that you were
saying with regard to people

00:40:14.810 --> 00:40:18.020
of color and your sense of
oppression and unfairness

00:40:18.020 --> 00:40:21.810
will show up in all of those
other instances as well.

00:40:21.810 --> 00:40:24.920
The net result of all
that is that if we've

00:40:24.920 --> 00:40:28.430
got to get Americans to
understand and believe

00:40:28.430 --> 00:40:32.512
that no one is free
until we all are.

00:40:32.512 --> 00:40:33.220
EDDIE HUANG: Yes.

